Muscles of the superior palate?
Tensor veli palatini: {{c1::tenses soft palate & opens auditory tube during swallowing or yawning (CN V3)}}
Levator veli palatini: {{c2::elevates soft palate during swallowing or yawning (CN X)}}
Uvular muscle: {{c3::elevates uvula against posterior pharyngeal wall during swallowing (CN X)}}

Muscles of the inferior palate?
Palatopharyngeus: {{c1::Palate to pharyngeal wall (pharyngeal muscle; CN X)}}
Palatoglossus:{{c2:: Palate to tongue (extrinsic tongue muscle; CN X)}}

Both palatine arch muscles are innervated by {{c1::CN X.}} When attempting to elevate the palate (e.g. saying “ahh”), a lesion would cause the soft palate to {{c2::sag on the affected side & the uvula to point to the contralateral side. }}

Oral Cavity includes: {{c1::teeth, gingivae, tongue, palate, palatine & lingual tonsils}}
Prepares food for ingestion, begins {{c2::swallowing process}}, important for {{c3::speech}}
The hypoglossal nerve (CN XII) provides motor innervation to all tongue muscles except {{c1::palatoglossus (CN X)}}
Hypoglossal n. passes between {{c1::mylohyoid and hyoglossus mm. to reach the tongue}}

PS pathway of fibers to submandibular/sublingual glands (written out-ignore if the visual pathway on other card works):
1.Preganglionic parasympathetic cell bodies located in {{c1::brainstem nuclei (superior salivary nucleus).}}
2.Preganglionic parasympathetic fibers travel {{c2::through the middle ear}} as the {{c3::chorda tympani branch of CN VII.}}
3.These fibers join the {{c4::lingual nerve}} in the {{c5::infratemporal fossa.}}
4.Synapse at the {{c6::submandibular ganglion.}}
5.Postganglionic parasympathetic fibers distribute to the {{c7::submandibular/sublingual glands}} via {{c8::lingual n. branches.}}

Pathway of sympathetic fibers to sublingual/submandibular gland (written out version)?
1.Preganglionic sympathetic cell bodies located in {{c1::lateral horn at T1-T4}}
2.Preganglionic sympathetic fibers ascend {{c2::sympathetic chain}} to {{c3::superior cervical ganglion (SCG)}}
3.Postganglionic sympathetic cell bodies are located in the {{c4::SCG}}
4.Postganglionic sympathetic fibers distribute via {{c5::external carotid nerve}}

Boundaries of the Nasopharynx:
Superior: {{c1::
Occipital bone
}}Anterior: {{c2::Choanae}}
Posterior: {{c3::CV 1 & 2}}
Inferior: {{c4::Soft palate}}

All laryngeal mm. innervated by inferior (recurrent) laryngeal n. (CN X)
except {{c1::cricothyroid (external branch of superior laryngeal n.; CN X)}}
Hard palate is part of {{c1::maxillary/palatine bone}}, soft palate is {{c2::posterior with no bone}}
